## Output & Report Generation

The pipeline must produce the following deliverables:

### Structured CSV Outputs (output/)
- feature_importance.csv – Ranked feature contributions to predictions
- population_shift_patterns.csv – ZIP-level projected changes
- retail_deficit_predictions.csv – Predicted retail gaps per ZIP
- scenario_predictions.csv – Forecasts under alternate economic scenarios
- scenario_summary.csv – Aggregated scenario impact overview
- retail_spending_leakage.csv – Estimated local economic leakage
- ten_year_growth_areas.csv – Forecasted long-term high-growth ZIPs
- emerging_housing_areas.csv – ZIPs with increased multi-family development
- retail_housing_opportunity.csv – ZIPs with high housing, low retail
- downtown_comparison.csv – Comparative ZIP-level metrics for central areas
- zip_summary.csv – Master ZIP-level summary
- high_leakage_areas.csv, lowest_retail_provision.csv, top_impacted_areas.csv – Targeted ZIP subsets
- model_metrics.csv – Model performance summary
- retail_deficit_feature_importance.csv – Feature importance for retail model

### Visualizations (output/visualizations/)
- permits_by_year.png, permits_by_community.png, permit_costs_distribution.png
- population_changes_distribution.png, median_income_trend.png, total_population_trend.png
- retail_deficit_feature_importance.png, top_retail_deficit_areas.png, housing_vs_retail_scatter.png
- Other scenario, trend, and impact plots

### Reports (output/reports/)
- EXECUTIVE_SUMMARY.md – Summary of findings
- chicago_population_analysis_report.md – Full technical report
- economic_impact_analysis.md – Economic condition impact study
- housing_retail_balance_report.md – Housing vs. retail development analysis
- chicago_zip_summary.md – ZIP-by-ZIP breakdown
- ten_year_growth_analysis.md – Long-term growth forecast

#### Optional Dashboard
- DASHBOARD.html – Interactive summary dashboard (if enabled)

